1
00:00:00,230 --> 00:00:06,230
Trong video này chúng ta sẽ so sánh vertical slice architecture với clean architecture.

2
00:00:06,770 --> 00:00:12,860
Vertical slice architecture nhấn mạnh việc tổ chức phát triển phần mềm xung quanh các tính năng, cắt

3
00:00:12,860 --> 00:00:15,290
đi qua tất cả các lớp theo cách vertical.

4
00:00:15,290 --> 00:00:19,400
Mỗi tính năng hoặc slice được phát triển và triển khai độc lập.

5
00:00:20,140 --> 00:00:26,320
Mặt khác, clean architecture tập trung vào separation of concerns và dependency rules.

6
00:00:26,350 --> 00:00:33,280
Nó tổ chức mã thành các lớp với các lớp ổn định nhất và business agnostic nhất ở trung tâm

7
00:00:33,280 --> 00:00:40,000
các entities, và use cases cũng như external concerns như UI và data access layers ở các lớp bên ngoài.

8
00:00:41,140 --> 00:00:43,090
Với vertical slice architecture.

9
00:00:43,090 --> 00:00:49,720
Các development teams tập trung vào việc cung cấp các tính năng hoàn chỉnh, mỗi tính năng có khả năng chạm tới tất cả các lớp

10
00:00:49,720 --> 00:00:50,620
của stack.

11
00:00:50,650 --> 00:00:58,030
Nó phù hợp chặt chẽ với agile methodologies nơi cung cấp các tính năng hoạt động, testable một cách nhanh chóng

12
00:00:58,030 --> 00:01:05,920
là chìa khóa, nhưng clean architecture ủng hộ một cách tiếp cận có cấu trúc hơn, đảm bảo rằng business

13
00:01:05,920 --> 00:01:08,920
logic được tách rời khỏi external concerns.

14
00:01:08,950 --> 00:01:14,380
Cách tiếp cận này có lợi cho khả năng bảo trì lâu dài và scalability.

15
00:01:15,410 --> 00:01:22,340
Vertical slice architecture tỏa sáng trong các kịch bản nơi rapid development và delivery của các independent

16
00:01:22,340 --> 00:01:23,870
features là quan trọng.

17
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:31,640
Nó phù hợp với agile teams làm việc trên các ứng dụng phức tạp với nhiều tính năng có thể thay đổi

18
00:01:31,640 --> 00:01:33,350
hoặc phát triển độc lập.

19
00:01:34,270 --> 00:01:41,050
Clean architecture là lý tưởng cho các ứng dụng quy mô lớn nơi bảo trì lâu dài và scalability

20
00:01:41,050 --> 00:01:46,990
và khả năng thích ứng với các yêu cầu kinh doanh hoặc công nghệ thay đổi là tối quan trọng.

21
00:01:47,020 --> 00:01:53,380
It ensures that core business logic remains unaffected by changes in the external layers.

22
00:01:54,530 --> 00:02:01,370
So once you choose vertical slice over the clean architecture, the first reason is rapid development

23
00:02:01,370 --> 00:02:02,450
and deployment.

24
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:09,410
When the priority is to develop and deploy features rapidly and independently, vertical slice is more

25
00:02:09,410 --> 00:02:10,220
appropriate.

26
00:02:10,550 --> 00:02:13,820
The second reason is agile and scrum teams.

27
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:20,690
For teams practicing the agile or scrum that need to deliver complete features in short cycles.

28
00:02:20,720 --> 00:02:24,140
Vertical Slice aligns well with these methodologies.

29
00:02:24,940 --> 00:02:27,670
And another reason is microservices.

30
00:02:27,670 --> 00:02:34,150
In a microservice architecture, where each service is often responsible for a distinct feature or business

31
00:02:34,150 --> 00:02:34,900
capability.

32
00:02:34,930 --> 00:02:37,960
Vertical slice can be particularly effective.

33
00:02:38,950 --> 00:02:46,180
So let's see our issue of microservices and compare with the catalog versus organic microservices catalog

34
00:02:46,180 --> 00:02:49,030
microservices using the vertical slice architecture.

35
00:02:49,060 --> 00:02:55,870
So in our issue of microservices, the catalog microservices manage the products categories and inventory.

36
00:02:55,870 --> 00:02:59,110
And it is using the vertical slice architecture.

37
00:02:59,230 --> 00:03:06,250
Each feature, like adding any product or updating inventory or managing categories, is developed as

38
00:03:06,250 --> 00:03:07,420
a separate slice.

39
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:15,040
Each slice would include its own API endpoint, business logic and data access code, allowing for the

40
00:03:15,040 --> 00:03:21,370
rapid development and updates to individual aspects of the product catalog without affecting the others.

41
00:03:22,070 --> 00:03:26,180
On the other hand, ordering microservices uses clean architecture.

42
00:03:26,180 --> 00:03:32,180
So ordering microservices handles order processing logic, including cart management, order placement

43
00:03:32,180 --> 00:03:34,190
and payment processing.

44
00:03:34,190 --> 00:03:41,120
With clean architecture, core business rules and use cases of order processing are central and

45
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:45,680
isolated from external concerns like database operations or UI.

46
00:03:45,980 --> 00:03:53,000
This separation ensures that important business rules remain stable and are not affected by changes in external systems,

47
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:56,480
such as payment gateways or database schema.

48
00:03:56,990 --> 00:04:02,870
So the choice between vertical slice architecture and clean architecture depends on specific requirements

49
00:04:02,870 --> 00:04:04,400
of the project.

50
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:11,270
Vertical slice focuses more on features and agility, and it is ideal for rapid feature development and

51
00:04:11,270 --> 00:04:12,170
deployment.

52
00:04:12,530 --> 00:04:18,980
Clean architecture is more suitable for large-scale, long-lived applications, where business rules

53
00:04:18,980 --> 00:04:22,250
must be isolated from external changes.

54
00:04:22,610 --> 00:04:28,970
We will use both architectures in different microservices that can leverage their strengths according to

55
00:04:28,970 --> 00:04:31,250
the requirements of each microservice.

